The National Working Committee (NWC) of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has appointed Governor Mai Mala Buni of Yobe  as the returning officer for the Bayelsa State  governorship primary election. A statement by the Director-General for Press Affairs to the governor, Abdullahi Bego, said the governor’s appointment was contained in a letter signed by the National Chairman of the party, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. “The primary election was originally scheduled for Thursday 29th August 2019 but shifted to Saturday 31st August 2019. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY “The appointment of His Excellency Governor Buni as returning officer was contained in a letter signed by the National Chairman of the party, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. “Consequently, His Excellency the governor will travel to Yenagoa, Bayelsa State on Friday 30th August 2019 in time for the primary election on Saturday. “The governor will return to office in Damaturu on Monday 2nd September 2019 at the end of his assignment.” the statement read. 2019: As submission of party candidates closes today Primaries: APC NEC allowed states to determine options APC to sue INEC over Zamfara, rejects Okorocha’s in-law Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin